<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"History">History</h2><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHeron%27s_formula&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: History"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The formula is credited to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hero=
_of_Alexandria" title=3D"Hero of Alexandria">Heron (or Hero) of Alexandria<=
/a> (<abbr title=3D"floruit ('flourished'&nbsp;=E2=80=93 known to have been=
 active at a particular time or during a particular period)">fl.</abbr> 60 =
AD),<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Heron%27s_formula#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and a proof can be f=
ound in his book <i>Metrica</i>. Mathematical historian <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Heath_(classicist)" title=3D"Thomas Heath (cla=
ssicist)">Thomas Heath</a> suggested that <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Archimedes" title=3D"Archimedes">Archimedes</a> knew the formula ov=
er two centuries earlier,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heron%27s_formula#cite_note-5"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 and since <i>Metrica</i> is a collection of the mathematical knowledge ava=
ilable in the ancient world, it is possible that the formula predates the r=
eference given in that work.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heron%27s_formula#cite_note-6"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up>
</p><p>A formula equivalent to Heron's was discovered by Chinese mathematic=
ian Qin Jiushao:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle A=3D{\frac {1}{2}}{\sqrt {a^{2}c^{2}-\left({\frac {a^{2=
}+c^{2}-b^{2}}{2}}\right)^{2}}},}">
  <semantics>
