</a> when computing with limited precision such as when using <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Floating-point_arithmetic" title=3D"Floating-po=
int arithmetic">floating-point arithmetic</a>. Such triangles have one or t=
wo sides whose length is very close to the semiperimeter, leading to <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catastrophic_cancellation" title=3D"Cata=
strophic cancellation">catastrophic cancellation</a>. A stable alternative =
involves arranging the lengths of the sides so that <span class=3D"mwe-math=
-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe=
-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.or=
g/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle a\geq b\geq c}">
